claims:
11. A method for non-invasively developing a decoder of an invasive brain computer interface (iBCI), the method comprising:
using, by a user, a motion capture device to capture kinematic data of the user;
receiving, by a processor in operable communication with the motion capture device, the kinematic data of the user;
utilizing, by the processor, an artificial neural network (ANN) to generate emulated neuron firing rates associated with the kinematic data; and
translating, by the processor, the emulated neuron firing rates to corresponding control commands for an external device of the iBCI, thereby obtaining the decoder.
